    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/1852a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 14, 1918—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3549. For Sheldon [from War Trade Board]: No. 1857. Repeat to Denmark and Sweden.
                    We have informed commercial Representative that from the point of view of
                    conservation we could now spare practically all articles and that we would
                    recommend to our associates an increase in the ration to such amounts as Denmark
                    (Sweden) might need under the new conditions, suggesting that any further needs
                    be laid before the Inter-Allied Committee at Copenhagen (Stockholm) for
                    transmission to the A.B.C. and thence to the various governments concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
